column10: The following report is for Margeret with the considered chat jezzebelle. The considered chat showed that Bacterial Level Counts were within range expected at 73.25. The upper reference range of 90.00 was not breached. The current range is near the average point of split, 77.50. The values being under the average show that the cause of pathology is likely not related to bacterial kinesis. Recommendations going forward as as follows : - Monitoring of viral load - Determination of allergens that may be related - Investigation of metabolic rates and factors.The following report is for Margeret with the considered chat jezzebelle.
